Privacy Policy
Anthony Hopkins built the HexaCalc app as a Free app. This service is provided by Anthony Hopkins at no cost and is intended for use as is.
​
This page is used to inform visitors regarding my policies with the collection, use, and disclosure of Personal Information if anyone decided to use my Service.
​
If you choose to use my Service, then you agree to the collection and use of information in relation to this policy.
HexaCalc does not collect any personal information from the user, the only data which is collected is the default data made available through Apple via the App Store Connect (crashes, downloads, App Store analytics, and usage). This basic data is not shared with any third parties or linked to your identity.
​
Changes to This Privacy Policy
I may update our Privacy Policy from time to time. Thus, you are advised to review this page periodically for any changes. I will notify you of any changes by posting the new Privacy Policy on this page.
This policy is effective as of 2022-04-13.
